Articles.Content: @Somgosomgo Please use pastebin instead of posting your log directly in the thread.

24 minutes ago, Vegemeister said:

@Somgosomgo Please use pastebin instead of posting your log directly in the thread.


Apparently, my PC really hates pasting large amounts of text in browsers to the point that I can barely do anything. Putting that spoiler in took a long time and then the reply to you contained my post as well for some reason. I had to erase that too. Not fun.

http://filebin.ca/2fWdBpVaRKMC/output_log.txt

Edited April 30, 2016 by Somgosomgo

6 minutes ago, Somgosomgo said:


Apparently, my PC really hates pasting large amounts of text in browsers to the point that I can barely do anything. Putting that spoiler in took a long time and then the reply to you contained my post as well for some reason. I had to erase that as well. Not fun.

Hmm.  I'm sorry to hear that.  I forgot about spoilers.

@Somgosomgo: I cannot reproduce any issues, I suggest you try reinstalling the your mods, particularly FAR without using any mod managers of any kind (including CKAN) and try again.  There is nothing in the log that points to framerate issues nor a cause for the crash, and the crash does not appear to be connected to FAR in any way.

@ferram4: I installed FAR manually. I'll reinstall KSP as well, run it with FAR only and check what happens.

EDIT: issue persists. I noticed that:
- It is actually stuttering and not low framerate.
- The stuttering disappears when KSP is not simulating - being in a different scene such as the space center or the VAB.

Edited April 30, 2016 by Somgosomgo
